}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== ===Warning=== It is ''NOT'' a regular WiFi card, but just a dumb ''"Companion RF module"'', to Gemini Lake :"Pulsar" CNVi IP-core. So it Is ''NOT'' backward-compatible in the all senses.
«Jefferson Peak» is an implementation of "Companion RF module" for AC-9560. :Description of "Pulsar" and CNVi overall idea: [https://en.wikichip.org/wiki/intel/cnvi CNVi] • [https://fccid.io/MSQ9560NG/User-Manual/9560NGW-User-Manual-3645263.pdf Details]
===HW features Requirements=== As it not a regular WiFi card it has as additional HW requirement :to support ''Pulsar'' IP-core.
Following [[Intel]] SoC devices include ''Pulsar'': :- Cannon Lake PCH-LP :- Cannon Lake PCH-H :- Gemini Lake {{FCC ST|01/21/2018|indexme.}}
